### **Day 2: Write Findings 1-2 (Volatility Focus)**
**Effort:** 3 hours | **Output:** Finding 1 (Volatility) + Finding 2 (Seasonal), ~800 words

**Finding 1: Revenue Volatility (Coefficient of Variation Analysis)**
- Chart: Figure 6.1.1 (Distribution of CV across SKUs)
- ORIR structure:
  - O: 770 SKUs (88%) show CV >25%, top 10 show 85-142%
  - R: Seasonal demand (beverages), festival cycles, category mix
  - I: ‚Çπ240k lost sales from stockouts + ‚Çπ176k overstock
  - R: Quadrant safety stock policy (Q1: 40%, Q2: 10%, Q3: 5%, Q4: 50%)

**Finding 2: Rolling Volatility Seasonal Pattern**
- Chart: Figure 6.1.2 (Time-series rolling œÉ with peak annotations)
- ORIR structure:
  - O: June peak rolling œÉ 52% vs July 28% baseline
  - R: Monsoon prep, festival stocking, post-season lull
  - I: June requires ‚Çπ2.22M inventory, procurement lead time critical
  - R: Procurement calendar: Order by Apr 15 for Jun peak

**Writing Tips:**
- Use elite phrasing from kit
- Start with O (most factual), end with R (forward-looking)
- Every metric quantified
- Each section 3-4 sentences

