### **Day 3: Write Findings 3-4 (Margin & Inventory Focus)**
**Effort:** 3 hours | **Output:** Finding 3 (Margin) + Finding 4 (ABC), ~800 words

**Finding 3: Low-Margin Product Concentration**
- Chart: Figure 6.2.1 (Margin histogram + top/bottom performers bar)
- ORIR structure:
  - O: 42 SKUs (48%) <15% margin; 3 SKUs negative margin
  - R: Strategic positioning (staples compete on price), pricing uniformity
  - I: ‚Çπ12.3k annual loss from loss-makers, ‚Çπ3:1 capital efficiency gap
  - R: Price increases (Salt +10%, Spices +17%), discontinue losses, bundling

**Finding 4: ABC Classification Pareto Distribution**
- Chart: Figure 6.3.1 (Pareto chart: bar revenue + cumulative line %)
- ORIR structure:
  - O: Class A 12 SKUs (14%) = 68% revenue; Class C 61 SKUs (70%) = 18%
  - R: Seasonal bestsellers, customer staples, niche fragmentation
  - I: Shelf allocation mismatch (Class A 18% space for 68% revenue)
  - R: Reallocate: Class A 28%, Class B 25%, Class C 22%

