## ‚úÖ QUALITY GATE: 10-POINT VERIFICATION

Before you submit Section 6, run this checklist:

**Content Quality:**
1. ‚úÖ ORIR completeness‚ÄîEvery finding has explicit Observation, Reason, Implication, Recommendation
2. ‚úÖ Quantified evidence‚Äî95%+ of claims backed by numbers (no "high", "significant", "some")
3. ‚úÖ Business implication‚ÄîEvery finding quantifies ‚Çπ at stake or opportunity size
4. ‚úÖ Actionable recommendation‚ÄîEvery recommendation includes phase, timeline, responsible party, success metric

**Visual & Data:**
5. ‚úÖ Chart integration‚ÄîEach finding has 1 supporting chart (Figure 6.X.X) with caption
6. ‚úÖ Data traceability‚ÄîEvery statistic linked to source CSV file
7. ‚úÖ Problem mapping‚ÄîEach finding explicitly addresses ‚â•1 of 4 problem objectives

**Professional Standards:**
8. ‚úÖ Tone & language‚Äî100% third-person professional, zero "I/we", passive voice where appropriate
9. ‚úÖ Word count‚ÄîTotal 2,400-2,900 words, balanced across 6 findings
10. ‚úÖ Formatting‚ÄîTimes New Roman 12pt, 1.5 spacing, justified alignment, page numbers

